            "summary": "A massive collection of more than 16 billion login credentials linked to major platforms like Apple, Google, and Facebook has emerged online, as reported by cybersecurity experts. This disclosure is considered one of the largest exposures of personal information to date. In the current year alone, researchers have identified 30 sizeable data sets, each containing anywhere from tens of millions to over 3.5 billion user credentials. The details, which were not previously reported, were temporarily visible due to misconfigured cloud storage or Elasticsearch instances, allowing researchers to identify them before they disappeared. This discovery highlights the concerning prevalence and sophistication of credential leaks, with data obtained from malicious software known as infostealers, which extract usernames, passwords, and session information.",
